The conference, the people were getting up early to go for runs. Yeah, it's way more

00:11:01.719 --> 00:11:09.479
healthy than people expect. Yeah. I know a lot of us might not be from a finance background

00:11:10.599 --> 00:11:16.520
and you can't give us any investment advice here, but I was just wondering, when you talk

00:11:16.520 --> 00:11:20.840
about risk management, could you just share a little bit with us on what that means?

00:11:21.799 --> 00:11:27.960
Sure. So the way to think about it is maybe from the other side of the table, which is the

00:11:27.960 --> 00:11:34.599
portfolio manager side. And you think about the investments that they want to make and the style

00:11:34.599 --> 00:11:42.840
that they have and how are they going to put risk on the table or money in terms of investments to

00:11:42.840 --> 00:11:51.719
stocks or to bonds? And then how do you kind of quantify the various outcomes of those exposures,

00:11:51.719 --> 00:11:57.640
those risks, those bets that they're taking in the same way that they would take it? And you want

00:11:57.640 --> 00:12:01.960
to be able to explain to them the risks that they're taking in the same way that they take

00:12:01.960 --> 00:12:07.719
risk. Two different teams might have different approaches and I'm not going to want to use the

00:12:07.719 --> 00:12:13.960
same language or presentation of how they're taking risks. I'm going to want to tailor it

00:12:14.679 --> 00:12:19.400
specifically there too. So just to maybe really apply a little example is, let's say you really

00:12:19.400 --> 00:12:25.400
like a stock, pick your favorite technology company that's based in the U.S. And just by saying those

00:12:25.400 --> 00:12:31.080
few terms, you can start thinking about different exposures that a company like that might have,

00:12:31.080 --> 00:12:36.359
you know, just general market exposure, just general equity market exposure. And then they're

00:12:36.359 --> 00:12:40.359
going to also have some U.S. equity market exposure. They're going to have some technology

00:12:40.359 --> 00:12:45.559
exposure. So those are three pretty high level risks already. And you have to figure out how

00:12:45.559 --> 00:12:51.000
much exposure or weight do they have to each of those. And then you can start thinking about,

00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:56.679
OK, what happens in this scenario? If that happens, you know, technology, you know,

00:12:56.679 --> 00:13:03.080
continues or doesn't in its current trend. And then you can start having those conversations

00:13:03.080 --> 00:13:07.400
with the portfolio manager and ask questions along the lines of, does, you know, does this

00:13:07.400 --> 00:13:12.679
surprise you? Is this what you'd expect? And it's more of a two way dialogue. And it can get kind of

00:13:12.679 --> 00:13:18.039
fun in a way, because especially when you have events coming up like elections, you can start

00:13:18.039 --> 00:13:24.200
thinking about who's going to, you know, what kind of impact each candidate have in terms of their

00:13:24.200 --> 00:13:29.080
policies and start thinking about, OK, what are they going to do here or there? And then what's

00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:35.640
my exposure to that factor? And then I can start thinking about, you know, how is that going to

00:13:35.640 --> 00:13:41.080
impact what I'm actually holding and have very similar conversations again with the portfolio

00:13:41.080 --> 00:13:46.599
manager. So thinking about the exposures to difference, you know, factor bets is what I've

00:13:46.599 --> 00:13:51.080
essentially been describing in a way. But at the end of the day, there's also a bunch of non-factor,

00:13:51.080 --> 00:13:57.799
more idiosyncratic SOX specific or asset class specific risks that are unique to that company

00:13:57.799 --> 00:14:02.520
as well. But, you know, for the most part, what I've been describing is more on that factor based

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:07.400
side. And you can start to think about those in the larger context of the markets and explaining

00:14:07.400 --> 00:14:12.039
those and thinking about that as a two way street with the portfolio manager.

00:14:15.080 --> 00:14:16.039
Awesome. Thank you.

